# Approval sidecar secrets (cp env.example .env -- gitignored). This is the ONLY
# container that holds the approval-channel credentials; tools never see them.
#
# Which platform delivers the Approve/Deny card: slack (default) or discord;
# telegram is planned. Approval is HUMAN-in-the-loop -- pick a platform (or at
# least an account) the agent does NOT operate. If the agent's own tools can
# read the card and press its buttons, the gate can approve itself and the
# whole control is theater. Concretely: don't use the telegram provider on the
# same account the telegram tool runs as; if your agent operates your Slack,
# use discord for approvals, and vice versa.
#APPROVAL_PROVIDER=slack
#
# Slack app setup (once, at https://api.slack.com/apps):
#  1. OAuth & Permissions -> scope `chat:write` -> install to workspace -> copy the
#     Bot User OAuth Token (xoxb-...) into SLACK_BOT_TOKEN.
#  2. Basic Information -> copy the Signing Secret into SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET.
#  3. Interactivity & Shortcuts -> ON -> Request URL:
#        https://approval.<MCP_DOMAIN>/slack/interact
#     (ONE URL for the whole stack -- this sidecar answers clicks for every tool.)
#  4. Make a (private) channel, invite the bot, put its channel ID in
#     SLACK_APPROVAL_CHANNEL.
#
# The Slack values are REQUIRED for approvals to work: the card is the only
# channel that reaches the human (no link goes to the chat -- it reads as prompt
# injection there). Without them, gated tools report the approval as undeliverable.
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=
SLACK_APPROVAL_CHANNEL=
#
# Discord app setup (once, at https://discord.com/developers/applications):
#  1. New Application -> Bot -> Reset Token -> copy into DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN.
#  2. General Information -> copy Public Key into DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY.
#  3. Installation/OAuth2 -> invite the bot to your server with the
#     "Send Messages" permission; make a private channel the bot can post in,
#     enable Developer Mode (User Settings -> Advanced), right-click the
#     channel -> Copy Channel ID into DISCORD_APPROVAL_CHANNEL_ID.
#  4. General Information -> Interactions Endpoint URL:
#        https://approval.<MCP_DOMAIN>/discord/interact
#     Set this LAST: Discord validates the endpoint (PING + a bad-signature
#     probe) the moment you save it, so the sidecar must already be live.
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=
DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY=
DISCORD_APPROVAL_CHANNEL_ID=
# Public base for the approval page linked from the Slack card (fallback if the
# buttons fail); the tunnel overlay stamps this from MCP_DOMAIN -- set it here
# only when running outside compose.
#APPROVAL_PUBLIC_URL=https://approval.<MCP_DOMAIN>
